<TITLE> Pintu, wife get bail in tax-dodge case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 7 (bdnews24.com) - The High Court Sunday granted three months' bail to former BNP lawmaker Nasiruddin Ahmed Pintu and his wife Nasima Akhter Kalpana on Sunday in a tax evasion case. A High Court bench of Justice Mirza Hossein Haider and Justice Mamnoon Rahman also stayed the proceedings of the case for three months. Representing the couple, senior advocate AJ Mohammad Ali told the court that the National Board of Revenue filed the tax evasion case last week with Dhaka senior special judge's court. But before filing such a case, the accused has to be given notice as per section 93 of the Income Tax Ordinance, the lawyer said The NBR filed the case against the couple without issuing the notice. Advocate Asaduzzaman, who assisted AJ Mohammad Ali in the hearing, told bdnews24.com there was another graft case against Pintu the proceedings of which have been stayed. Bail will also be sought in the case. Assistant attorney general Zafar Imam represented the NBR. Former law minister Moudud Ahmed and former state minister Mir Nasir Uddin also applied for bail in income tax evasion cases on Sunday. The bail prayers have been filed with the same High Court bench. bdnew
